                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-038-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 36:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >וַיַּעַן־יְהוָה אֶת־אִיֹּוב מִן הַסְּעָרָה וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 36:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi H
                                Ijovɣa ol davuldan da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi H
                                Ijovɣa ol davuldan da ajtty</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv
                                berdi H osol Ijovɣa tavul asyra da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Tenri Ijovha ol tavuldan da
                            ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-038-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>bavyn anyn</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">חֲתֻלָּתֹו </foreign>
                            ‘its swaddling band’, added after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר </foreign>
                            ‘or say’. | C: <emph>čurɣanmaɣy</emph>. | QB: <emph>čurɣanmaɣy</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>čörgevin anyn</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>č́orǵav́uń</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-038-fn3" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>bilek</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-038-fn4" type="footnote">JSul.I.04:
                            <emph>ajyrylady</emph>; a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-038-fn5" type="footnote">JSul.I.04:
                                <emph>češilermusen</emph>; a scribal error.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
